    "title_zh": "怎样祷告？",
    "title_en": "How to Pray?",
    "content_zh": "祷告就是和上帝说话，就像跟一个最亲密的朋友聊天一样。不需要用特别高深的词，也不需要固定的姿势。你可以随时随地祷告——在上学路上、考试前、开心的时候、难过的时候。\n\n如何开始？ 找个安静的地方和时间，不需要特别的位置，但减少干扰会有帮助。从简单的开始：「上帝，我想和祢说话。」不需要华丽的语言——开心、担心、感恩、困惑，什么都可以跟祂说。上帝已经知道你的心，祂想听的是你真实的声音。\n\nACTS祷告法： 一个简单的方法是ACTS（赞美-认罪-感恩-祈求）模式：A-赞美：感谢上帝是谁；C-认罪：诚实地承认自己做错的事；T-感恩：感谢上帝的恩典；S-祈求：把你的需要告诉祂。\n\n祷告也要聆听。 祷告不只是说话，也要安静等候。祷告后花些时间安静下来，让圣灵对你的心说话。\n\n不用担心形式。 大声祷告、默祷都行，长的短的都行。五分钟真诚的祷告胜过半小时空洞的话语。记住，祷告不是在念咒语，上帝不是自动售货机。祂是你的天父，祂更在意你的心，而不是你的措辞。有时候上帝的回答是'是'，有时候是'还没有'，有时候是'我有更好的计划'——但祂一定会回应。",
    "content_en": "Prayer is just talking to God — like chatting with your closest friend. You don't need fancy words or a special posture. You can pray anytime, anywhere — on the way to school, before a test, when you're happy, when you're sad.\n\nHow to start? Find a quiet place and time. No special location needed, but avoiding distractions helps. Start with a simple acknowledgment: \"God, I want to talk to You.\" No fancy words needed — excitement, worry, gratitude, confusion — bring it all. God already knows your heart; He just wants to hear your genuine voice.\n\nThe ACTS method: A simple framework: A-Adoration (praise God for who He is), C-Confession (honestly admit what you've done wrong), T-Thanksgiving (thank God for His blessings), S-Supplication (tell Him what you need).\n\nPrayer is also listening. Prayer isn't just talking — it's also waiting quietly. After praying, spend time in silence and let God's Spirit speak to your heart.\n\nDon't worry about format. Pray out loud or silently, long or short — it all counts. Five minutes of sincere prayer beats half an hour of empty words. Remember, prayer isn't casting a spell, and God isn't a vending machine. He's your heavenly Father who cares about your heart, not your vocabulary. Sometimes God's answer is 'yes,' sometimes 'not yet,' and sometimes 'I have a better plan' — but He always responds.",
