    "title_zh": "为什么要读圣经？",
    "title_en": "Why Read the Bible?",
    "content_zh": "圣经不是一本普通的书——它是上帝写给你的信。在这个充满噪音的世界，圣经是你能听到上帝声音的地方。\n\n为什么要读圣经？\n\n1）认识上帝。 你想了解一个人，就要听他说话、读他写的东西。圣经就是上帝向我们说的话，通过它你会越来越了解上帝的性格、祂的爱、祂的计划。\n\n2）认识自己。 圣经像一面镜子，帮助你看清自己——你的价值、你的问题、你被造的目的。「神的道是活泼的，是有功效的，比一切两刃的剑更快。」（希伯来书4:12）\n\n3）生命的指南。 面对选择、困惑、压力时，圣经给你智慧和方向。「你的话是我脚前的灯，是我路上的光。」（诗篇119:105）\n\n4）属灵的食粮。 就像身体需要食物，灵魂需要上帝的话语来成长。不读圣经的基督徒就像不吃饭的人——会越来越虚弱。\n\n5）抵挡试探。 耶稣在旷野受试探时，用圣经的话来抵挡魔鬼。你也需要这个武器。\n\n6）经历上帝的同在。 很多人在读经时感受到上帝的安慰、引导和力量。圣经不只是信息，更是与上帝相遇的途径。\n\n每次读都会有新的收获，因为这是上帝活泼的话语！",
    "content_en": "The Bible isn't an ordinary book — it's God's letter to you. In a world full of noise, the Bible is where you can hear God's voice.\n\nWhy read the Bible?\n\n1) To know God. To understand someone, you listen to them and read what they've written. The Bible is God speaking to us — through it, you'll grow to understand His character, His love, and His plan.\n\n2) To know yourself. The Bible is like a mirror, helping you see clearly — your worth, your struggles, your purpose. \"The word of God is alive and active, sharper than any double-edged sword.\" (Hebrews 4:12)\n\n3) A guide for life. When facing choices, confusion, or pressure, the Bible gives you wisdom and direction. \"Your word is a lamp for my feet, a light on my path.\" (Psalm 119:105)\n\n4) Spiritual nourishment. Just as your body needs food, your soul needs God's Word to grow. A Christian who doesn't read the Bible is like a person who doesn't eat — they'll grow weaker.\n\n5) Resisting temptation. When Jesus was tempted in the wilderness, He used Scripture to fight back. You need this weapon too.\n\n6) Experiencing God's presence. Many people encounter God's comfort, guidance, and strength while reading Scripture. The Bible isn't just information — it's a pathway to meeting God.\n\nEvery time you read, you'll discover something new, because this is God's living Word!",
