    "id": "youth-006",
    "category": "校园生活",
    "section": "campus",
    "title_zh": "同学嘲笑我的信仰怎么办？",
    "title_en": "What If Classmates Mock My Faith?",
    "content_zh": "在学校里因为信仰被嘲笑真的很难受，但你不是一个人。耶稣自己说过：'世人若恨你们，你们知道恨你们以先，已经恨我了'（约翰福音15:18）。使徒们也被人认为是'疯子'。这不是你的失败，反而证明你在走正确的路。\n\n如何回应？\n\n1）不要用愤怒回应。 试着用温柔和尊重来面对（彼得前书3:15）。你可以说：'我理解你的看法，但这对我很重要。'有时候沉默反而是最有力的回应。\n\n2）记住你的身份。 你是上帝的孩子，你的价值不是由同学的评价决定的。他们嘲笑的不是你，而是你所信的。\n\n3）找到你的团队。 教会的青少年团契、基督徒同学、信任的导师——不要独自承受。找到支持你的人。\n\n4）装备自己。 学习如何回答常见的质疑。不是每个辩论都值得参与，但心里有预备会让你更有信心。\n\n5）为嘲笑你的人祷告。 这能软化你的心，也可能改变他们。有时候，嘲笑的背后其实是好奇。\n\n6）选择你的战场。 不是每次挑衅都需要回应。要有智慧——有时候你忠心、温柔的生命见证比任何辩论都更有力。你的生活可能是他们认识上帝的第一步。",
    "content_en": "Being mocked at school for your faith really hurts, but you're not alone. Jesus Himself said: 'If the world hates you, know that it hated me before it hated you' (John 15:18). The apostles were thought 'crazy' too. This isn't your failure — it actually proves you're on the right path.\n\nHow to respond?\n\n1) Don't respond with anger. Try gentleness and respect (1 Peter 3:15). You can say, 'I understand your view, but this is important to me.' Sometimes silence is the most powerful response.\n\n2) Remember your identity. You're a child of God, and your worth isn't determined by classmates' opinions. They're mocking what you believe, not who you are.\n\n3) Find your crew. Church youth group, Christian friends, trusted mentors — don't bear this alone. Find people who support you.\n\n4) Equip yourself. Learn to answer common challenges. Not every argument is worth engaging, but being prepared gives you confidence.\n\n5) Pray for those who mock you. This softens your heart and might change theirs. Sometimes mockery is actually curiosity in disguise.\n\n6) Choose your battles wisely. Not every provocation needs a response. Your faithful, gentle life witness is often more powerful than any debate. You might be their first step toward knowing God.",
