    "id": "youth-007",
    "category": "校园生活",
    "section": "campus",
    "title_zh": "科学和信仰矛盾吗？",
    "title_en": "Does Science Contradict Faith?",
    "content_zh": "很多人觉得科学和信仰是对立的，但事实并非如此！历史上许多伟大的科学家都是基督徒——牛顿、法拉第、帕斯卡等等。科学研究的是'怎么运作'（怎么），信仰回答的是'为什么存在'（为什么）。它们不是互相矛盾，而是互相补充。比如，科学可以告诉你水的化学成分是H₂O，但科学不能告诉你生命的意义是什么。宇宙的精密设计、自然规律的稳定性，反而指向一位智慧的创造者。需要注意的是，宏观进化论仍然只是一个假说，面临着许多科学挑战（如寒武纪大爆发、生物信息的起源等），它并没有被'证实'。微观进化（物种内的适应变化）是可以观察到的，但从单细胞到人类的宏观进化从未被直接观察。大爆炸理论则指向宇宙有一个开始——这恰恰与圣经'起初上帝创造天地'一致。上帝创造了可以被科学研究的世界，科学其实是在探索上帝的作品！",
    "content_en": "Many people think science and faith are opposites, but that's not true! Many of history's greatest scientists were Christians — Newton, Faraday, Pascal, and more. Science studies 'how things work,' while faith answers 'why things exist.' They're not contradictory — they're complementary. For example, science can tell you water is H₂O, but it can't tell you the meaning of life. The fine-tuning of the universe and the stability of natural laws actually point to an intelligent Creator. It's important to note that macro-evolution remains only a hypothesis, facing many scientific challenges (such as the Cambrian Explosion, the origin of biological information, etc.) — it has NOT been 'proven.' Micro-evolution (adaptive changes within species) is observable, but macro-evolution from single cells to humans has never been directly observed. The Big Bang theory actually points to the universe having a beginning — which is consistent with the Bible's 'In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth.' God created a world that CAN be studied by science. Science is actually exploring God's handiwork!",
