    "title_en": "How to Handle Exam Stress?",
    "content_zh": "考试压力是真实的，特别是面对升学考试，上帝理解你的感受。但记住：你的价值不是由分数定义的，你的身份不是由成绩决定的。\n\n实用建议：\n\n1）做好准备。 信仰不是让你不学习然后等奇迹。认真学习、合理规划、寻求帮助——该复习的还是要复习，这是忠心管理上帝给你的才能。\n\n2）祷告交托。 '应当一无挂虑，只要凡事藉着祷告、祈求和感谢，将你们所要的告诉上帝。'（腓立比书4:6）考前花一分钟安静祷告，深呼吸，把心交给祂。祷告不是迷信，而是与造物主对话。\n\n3）保持健康。 充足的睡眠、适当的运动、合理的饮食——照顾上帝给你的身体。\n\n4）调整心态。 尽力而为，结果交给上帝。一次考试失败不会毁掉你的人生。上帝对你的计划远大于一次考试，比你想象的更美好。\n\n5）不要忽略属灵操练。 不要因为学习忙就忽略了读经祷告。越是压力大，越需要从上帝那里支取力量。\n\n6）互相鼓励。 和朋友一起复习，互相祷告，分享你平安的秘诀。压力不需要一个人扛。\n\n努力学习，但不要让学业成为偶像。",
    "content_en": "Exam stress is real, especially facing entrance exams, and God understands how you feel. But remember: your worth isn't defined by your grades, and your identity isn't determined by test scores.\n\nPractical tips:\n\n1) Prepare well. Faith doesn't mean you skip studying and wait for a miracle. Study hard, plan wisely, seek help — being a faithful steward of the abilities God gave you.\n\n2) Pray and surrender. 'Be anxious for nothing, but in everything by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to God.' (Philippians 4:6) Take a minute before the exam to pray quietly and breathe. Prayer isn't superstition — it's conversation with the Creator.\n\n3) Stay healthy. Enough sleep, some exercise, good food — take care of the body God gave you.\n\n4) Adjust your mindset. Do your best, leave the results to God. One test failure won't ruin your life. God's plan for you is way bigger than one exam and better than you imagine.\n\n5) Don't neglect spiritual disciplines. Don't skip Bible reading and prayer because you're busy studying. The more pressure you face, the more you need strength from God.\n\n6) Encourage each other. Study with friends, pray for each other, share your secret of peace. You don't have to carry the pressure alone.\n\nWork hard, but don't make academics an idol.",
