    "title_zh": "如何交到好朋友？",
    "title_en": "How to Find Good Friends?",
    "content_zh": "圣经说：'滥交朋友的，自取败坏；但有一朋友，比弟兄更亲密'（箴言18:24）。朋友的影响力巨大，特别是在青少年时期。好的朋友会帮助你成长，而不是把你拉远离上帝。\n\n怎么找到好朋友？\n\n1）先做一个好朋友。 主动关心别人，倾听别人，真诚待人。\n\n2）区分密友和普通朋友。 密友应该是支持你信仰成长的人，即使不是基督徒，至少要尊重你的信仰。普通朋友可以包括各种人，这也是传福音的机会。\n\n3）参加教会青少年团契。 这里有一群跟你有同样信仰的同龄人，属灵友谊会帮助你成长。\n\n4）不要害怕跟非基督徒做朋友。 耶稣也跟'罪人'一起吃饭。关键是你影响他们，而不是被他们影响。参与健康的活动，避免试探的场合。\n\n5）学会设立界限。 如果一段友谊总是让你做违背良心的事，那要勇敢说不。不要为了受欢迎而妥协原则——真正的朋友会接受真实的你。\n\n6）记住你也在影响别人。 问问自己：我是帮助朋友更接近上帝，还是更远离上帝？\n\n最重要的：耶稣是你最好的朋友。在你孤单的时候，祂永远不会离开你。好的友谊需要时间，不要着急。",
    "content_en": "The Bible says, 'One who has unreliable friends soon comes to ruin, but there is a friend who sticks closer than a brother' (Proverbs 18:24). Friends have huge influence, especially during teenage years. Good friends help you grow and don't pull you away from God.\n\nHow to find good friends?\n\n1) BE a good friend first. Care for others, listen, be genuine.\n\n2) Distinguish close friends from casual friends. Close friends should support your faith growth — even if not Christians, they should at least respect your faith. Casual friends can include various people, and that's an evangelism opportunity too.\n\n3) Join a church youth group. You'll find peers who share your faith. Spiritual friendships help you grow.\n\n4) Don't be afraid to befriend non-Christians. Jesus ate with 'sinners' too. The key is that you influence them, not the other way around. Participate in healthy activities, avoid tempting situations.\n\n5) Learn to set boundaries. If a friendship keeps pushing you to do things against your conscience, have the courage to say no. Don't compromise principles to be popular — real friends accept the real you.\n\n6) Remember you're also influencing others. Ask yourself: am I helping friends move closer to or further from God?\n\nMost importantly: Jesus is your best friend. When you're lonely, He will never leave you. Good friendships take time — don't rush it.",
