    "title_en": "Social Media and Faith",
    "content_zh": "社交媒体是一个工具——它本身不是坏的，但可以被用好也可以被用坏。作为基督徒，如何智慧地使用它？\n\n1）比较是快乐的小偷。 当你刷到别人的'完美生活'，记住那只是精心挑选的片段。你的价值在上帝面前已经被完全确定了，不需要跟任何人比较。\n\n2）管理你的时间。 社交媒体容易成瘾，偷走我们与上帝和真实人际关系的时间。如果你花在手机上的时间比跟上帝相处的时间多得多，需要调整了。设定界限，定期'禁食'社交媒体。\n\n3）小心你消费的内容。 不合适的内容会悄悄影响你的思想。'你们要谨守你们的心'（箴言4:23）。发布前也问自己：这会让人更认识基督吗？避免抱怨、炫耀、传谣言。'污秽的言语一句不可出口，只要随事说造就人的好话。'\n\n4）积极使用。 分享鼓励的经文、恩典的见证、有意义的内容，传播正能量。社交媒体也是见证的新平台。\n\n5）避免网络争论。 特别是关于政治或争议话题，私下对话比公开辩论更有效。\n\n6）线下关系更重要。 再多的点赞也比不上一个真实的拥抱。定期放下手机，和真实的人在一起。\n\n记住：网络留痕永远存在，今天发的内容十年后还可能被看到。",
    "content_en": "Social media is a tool — it's not bad in itself, but it can be used well or poorly. As a Christian, how do you use it wisely?\n\n1) Comparison is the thief of joy. When you see others' 'perfect lives,' remember those are curated highlights. Your worth is already fully established before God — no comparison needed.\n\n2) Manage your time. Social media is addictive, stealing time from God and real relationships. If you spend way more time on your phone than with God, it's time to adjust. Set boundaries, regularly 'fast' from social media.\n\n3) Be careful what you consume. Inappropriate content quietly shapes your thinking. 'Guard your heart' (Proverbs 4:23). Before posting, ask yourself: will this help people know Christ better? Avoid complaining, showing off, spreading rumors. 'Let no unwholesome word proceed from your mouth, but only what builds others up.'\n\n4) Use it positively. Share encouraging verses, grace testimonies, meaningful content. Social media is also a new platform for witness.\n\n5) Avoid online arguments. Especially about politics or controversial topics — private conversations are more effective than public debates.\n\n6) Offline relationships matter more. No amount of likes beats a real hug. Regularly put down your phone and be with real people.\n\nRemember: the internet leaves permanent traces — what you post today might be seen ten years from now.",
