    "title_zh": "分享你的信仰",
    "title_en": "Sharing Your Faith",
    "content_zh": "分享信仰（传福音）可能是很多基督徒觉得最难的事。'如果被拒绝怎么办？''如果说错了怎么办？''我又不是牧师。'但记住：恐惧不是来自上帝的，而你有最好的消息——永生、赦免、盼望！\n\n克服恐惧的真理：\n你不需要是神学家才能分享。最有力的见证就是你自己的故事。\n结果不是你的责任——你的工作是撒种，圣灵负责让种子发芽。\n拒绝福音不是拒绝你——他们拒绝的是耶稣，不要往心里去。\n\n如何分享你的见证：\n你的个人见证通常有三个部分：信主前（你的生活、挣扎）、信主时（怎么遇见基督、什么打动了你）、信主后（生命有了什么改变）。即使从小在基督徒家庭长大，你的见证也可以是信仰从「父母的」变成「我自己的」的过程。保持真实，不要夸张；聚焦在基督做了什么；练习用2-3分钟讲完。\n\n实用技巧：\n1）先建立关系——人们不在乎你知道多少，直到他们知道你有多在乎。\n2）自然地分享——不需要硬塞，在聊天中自然提到。用对方能理解的语言，避免太多教会术语。\n3）学会倾听——了解对方的想法和需要，然后用福音来回应。\n4）随时预备——'常作准备，好回答每一个问你们心中盼望缘由的人'（彼得前书3:15）。\n5）从小事开始——邀请朋友参加教会活动、在困难时提到祷告。\n6）靠圣灵——改变人心是上帝的工作，不是你的。求圣灵给你机会、话语和勇气。\n\n传福音最大的秘诀：真诚的爱。当人们感受到你真的关心他们时，他们更愿意听。失败了又怎样？天不会塌。但如果成功了呢？永恒都会不同！",
    "content_en": "Sharing your faith (evangelism) might feel like the hardest thing for many Christians. 'What if I get rejected?' 'What if I say the wrong thing?' 'I'm not a pastor.' But remember: fear doesn't come from God, and you have the best news — eternal life, forgiveness, hope!\n\nTruths to overcome fear:\nYou don't need to be a theologian. The most powerful testimony is YOUR story.\nThe outcome isn't your responsibility — you plant seeds; the Spirit makes them grow.\nRejecting the Gospel isn't rejecting you — they're rejecting Jesus, not you personally.\n\nHow to share your testimony:\nA good testimony has three parts: before Christ (your life, struggles), meeting Christ (how you encountered Him, what moved you), after Christ (how life has changed). Even if you grew up in a Christian family, your testimony can be about faith becoming 'my own' rather than 'my parents'.' Stay authentic, don't exaggerate; focus on what Christ did; practice telling it in 2-3 minutes.\n\nPractical tips:\n1) Build relationships first — people don't care how much you know until they know how much you care.\n2) Share naturally — don't force it. Bring it up in conversation. Use language your audience understands, avoid church jargon.\n3) Learn to listen — understand what the other person thinks and needs, then connect the Gospel to that.\n4) Always be ready — 'Always be prepared to give an answer to everyone who asks you to give the reason for the hope that you have' (1 Peter 3:15).\n5) Start small — invite friends to church events, mention prayer during tough times.\n6) Rely on the Spirit — changing hearts is God's job, not yours. Ask for opportunities, words, and courage.\n\nThe biggest secret of evangelism: genuine love. When people feel you truly care, they're more willing to listen. What if you fail? The world won't end. But what if you succeed? Eternity will be different!",
