    "title_zh": "三位一体简单解释",
    "title_en": "The Trinity Made Simple",
    "content_zh": "三位一体听起来很复杂，但其实是基督教最美丽的真理之一。上帝是一位神，但祂同时以三个位格存在：圣父、圣子（耶稣）、圣灵。不是三个神，也不是一个神在演三个角色，而是一个神性、三个位格同时存在的奥秘。\n\n想象一下阳光：太阳本身、光线、温暖——不可分割，却又可以分辨。不过所有的比喻都不完美，因为三位一体超越了我们日常的经验。特别要注意：水的三种状态（冰、水、蒸汽）这个常见比喻其实是错误的，因为水在同一时间只能是一种状态，但三位一体的三个位格是同时存在的。\n\n三个位格各有什么角色？ 圣父是创造者和计划者，圣子耶稣是救赎者和道路，圣灵是安慰者和引导者。他们同等重要，本质相同，但功能不同。圣父创造了我们，圣子拯救了我们，圣灵住在我们里面。\n\n当你祷告时， 你向圣父祷告，因着耶稣的名，靠着圣灵的帮助——三个位格都参与在你和上帝的关系中。\n\n为什么这很重要？ 因为这告诉我们上帝的本质就是关系和爱。三位一体内部有完美的爱的交流，我们也被邀请参与这种爱的关系中。上帝理解关系、理解团体，因为祂自己就是完美的关系。认识三位一体不只是知识，更是认识那位深爱你的上帝是怎样的一位神。",
    "content_en": "The Trinity sounds complicated, but it's actually one of Christianity's most beautiful truths. God is one God, but He exists simultaneously as three persons: Father, Son (Jesus), and Holy Spirit. Not three gods, nor one God playing three roles, but one divine nature in three persons existing at the same time — a profound mystery.\n\nThink of sunlight: the sun itself, the light rays, the warmth — inseparable yet distinguishable. Though all analogies are imperfect, because the Trinity transcends our everyday experience. One common but misleading analogy is water's three states (ice, liquid, steam) — this actually teaches the heresy of modalism, since water can only be in one state at a time, while the three persons of the Trinity exist simultaneously.\n\nWhat are their roles? The Father is the Creator and Planner, Jesus the Son is the Redeemer and Way, the Holy Spirit is the Comforter and Guide. They're equally important, same essence, but different functions. The Father created us, the Son saved us, the Spirit lives in us.\n\nWhen you pray, you pray to the Father, in Jesus' name, with the Spirit's help — all three persons are involved in your relationship with God.\n\nWhy does this matter? Because it tells us that God's very essence is relationship and love. Within the Trinity, there's perfect loving communion, and we're invited into this loving relationship too. God understands relationships and community because He IS perfect relationship. Knowing the Trinity isn't just theology — it's knowing what kind of God deeply loves you.",
