    "id": "youth-022",
    "category": "信仰基础",
    "section": "faith-basics",
    "title_zh": "圣经是什么？",
    "title_en": "What is the Bible?",
    "content_zh": "圣经不是一本书，而是一个图书馆！它包含66本书，由大约40位作者在1500年间写成。但神奇的是，这些书有一个统一的主题：上帝的救赎计划。\n\n圣经分为旧约（39本）和新约（27本）。旧约讲的是上帝与以色列民的约定，预言救世主的到来。新约讲的是耶稣的生平、死亡、复活，以及早期教会的建立。整本圣经都指向一个人：耶稣基督。\n\n圣经是\"神所默示的\"（提摩太后书3:16），意思是圣灵引导人类作者写下神想要告诉我们的话。这不是机械式的听写，而是神通过每个作者的个性、背景、写作风格来传达真理。\n\n圣经不是科学教科书或历史百科全书，而是神的启示书。它的目的是告诉我们：神是谁、我们是谁、罪的问题、救恩的道路。当我们带着信心和祷告的心读圣经时，圣灵会向我们说话。",
    "content_en": "The Bible isn't one book — it's a library! It contains 66 books, written by about 40 authors over 1,500 years. But amazingly, these books have one unified theme: God's plan of salvation.\n\nThe Bible is divided into Old Testament (39 books) and New Testament (27 books). The Old Testament tells about God's covenant with Israel and prophesies the coming Messiah. The New Testament tells about Jesus' life, death, resurrection, and the early church. The whole Bible points to one person: Jesus Christ.\n\nThe Bible is \"God-breathed\" (2 Timothy 3:16), meaning the Holy Spirit guided human authors to write what God wanted to tell us. This wasn't mechanical dictation, but God communicating truth through each author's personality, background, and writing style.\n\nThe Bible isn't a science textbook or history encyclopedia — it's God's revelation book. Its purpose is to tell us: who God is, who we are, the problem of sin, and the way of salvation. When we read with faith and prayer, the Holy Spirit speaks to us through it.",
