    "id": "youth-023",
    "category": "信仰基础",
    "section": "faith-basics",
    "title_zh": "教会为什么重要？",
    "title_en": "Why is Church Important?",
    "content_zh": "很多人觉得\"我可以在家信神\"，为什么要去教会？这就像说\"我可以在家踢球\"但不参加球队一样。信仰不是个人独奏，而是交响乐团合作。\n\n教会是基督的身体，我们每个人都是其中的肢体（哥林多前书12:27）。手不能对脚说\"我不需要你\"，基督徒也不能独自成长。在教会里，我们可以：一起敬拜赞美神，彼此鼓励和代祷，一起学习圣经，使用恩赐服事他人，接受牧者的教导和关怀。\n\n当然，教会不完美——因为里面都是罪人！但这正是我们需要它的原因。在不完美的团体中学习爱和被爱，学习饶恕和被饶恕，这才是真正的属灵成长。\n\n不去教会的基督徒就像不吃饭的人——可能暂时不会死，但肯定不会健康。找一个忠于圣经、充满爱心的教会，委身其中，你会发现这是神给你最好的礼物之一。",
    "content_en": "Many people think \"I can believe in God at home\" — why go to church? That's like saying \"I can kick a ball at home\" but never joining a team. Faith isn't a solo performance; it's symphony orchestra collaboration.\n\nThe church is Christ's body, and we're each part of it (1 Corinthians 12:27). The hand can't say to the foot \"I don't need you,\" and Christians can't grow alone either. In church, we can: worship and praise God together, encourage and pray for each other, study Scripture together, serve others with our gifts, receive pastoral teaching and care.\n\nSure, church isn't perfect — it's full of sinners! But that's exactly why we need it. Learning to love and be loved in an imperfect community, learning to forgive and be forgiven — that's real spiritual growth.\n\nA Christian without church is like a person who doesn't eat — they might not die immediately, but they definitely won't be healthy. Find a Bible-faithful, loving church, commit to it, and you'll discover it's one of God's best gifts to you.",
