    "title_en": "How to Read the Bible (Methodology)",
    "content_zh": "读圣经不是读小说，需要一些方法。这里介绍「归纳法查经」——观察、解释、应用。\n\n第一步：观察 (观察)\n仔细阅读经文，问：\"这段经文说了什么？\"注意关键词、重复的字、对比、人物、地点、时间。别急着下结论，先收集信息。\n\n第二步：解释 (解释) \n经文的原意是什么？考虑：历史背景、文化背景、上下文、文体（诗歌、叙述、书信等）。问：\"作者想表达什么？原来的读者会怎么理解？\"\n\n第三步：应用 (应用)\n这段经文对今天的我有什么意义？神要我：知道什么真理？改变什么态度？采取什么行动？停止什么行为？\n\n实用技巧：\n每次读前先祷告\n用笔记本记录观察和想法\n一次专注一小段（5-10节）\n多读几遍，每次会有新发现\n找一本好的注释书帮助理解\n和别人分享讨论\n\n记住：圣经是神的话，圣灵是最好的老师！",
    "content_en": "Reading the Bible isn't like reading a novel — you need some methods. Here's the \"inductive Bible study\" approach: Observation, Interpretation, Application.\n\nStep 1: Observation\nRead carefully and ask: \"What does this text say?\" Notice keywords, repeated words, contrasts, characters, places, times. Don't rush to conclusions — gather information first.\n\nStep 2: Interpretation\nWhat did the text originally mean? Consider: historical background, cultural context, literary context, genre (poetry, narrative, epistle, etc.). Ask: \"What did the author want to communicate? How would original readers understand this?\"\n\nStep 3: Application\nWhat does this text mean for me today? What does God want me to: know (truth), change (attitude), do (action), stop (behavior)?\n\nPractical Tips:\nPray before reading\nUse a notebook for observations and thoughts\nFocus on small sections (5-10 verses) at a time\nRead multiple times — you'll discover something new each time\nGet a good commentary for help\nShare and discuss with others\n\nRemember: The Bible is God's Word, and the Holy Spirit is the best teacher!",
