    "title_en": "How to Be a Christian at School",
    "content_zh": "在学校做基督徒，不是要你站在桌子上大喊\"我信耶稣！\"，而是要活出基督的样式。你的生活就是你最好的见证。\n\n在学业上：\n诚实考试，不作弊\n按时完成作业，为神的荣耀努力——学习是对上帝创造的探索，无论数学、科学、文学、历史，都能显明上帝的荣耀和智慧\n帮助同学学习，分享笔记，用所学的知识帮助别人\n尊重老师，即使你不同意他们的观点\n追求卓越而不是完美主义——上帝要我们尽力，但好成绩是恩典，坏成绩不是咒诅\n\n在人际关系上：\n对每个人都友善，包括被边缘化的同学\n不参与恶意八卦和霸凌\n在冲突中做和平使者\n用行动显示什么叫\"爱人如己\"\n\n在价值观上：\n温和但坚定地表达你的信仰立场\n不用\"基督教术语\"吓跑别人，用正常语言分享\n为朋友祷告，但不强迫他们信教\n活出喜乐和平安，让人好奇你为什么不一样\n\n在品格塑造上：\n在困难学科中学习坚持，在容易学科中学习谦卑\n品格的培养比知识的积累更重要\n学习技能也是服侍的装备——未来无论做什么工作，都可以荣耀上帝\n\n记住：你可能是某些同学认识的唯一基督徒。他们对基督教的印象很可能来自于你。不用完美，但要真实。当你犯错时，勇敢道歉；当有机会时，自然分享你的信仰。",
    "content_en": "Being a Christian at school doesn't mean standing on desks shouting \"I believe in Jesus!\" — it means living like Christ. Your life is your best testimony.\n\nIn academics:\nBe honest in exams, don't cheat\nComplete assignments on time, work hard for God's glory — learning explores God's creation; whether math, science, literature, or history, all can reveal God's glory and wisdom\nHelp classmates study, share notes, use your knowledge to help others\nRespect teachers, even when you disagree with their views\nPursue excellence, not perfectionism — God wants our best effort, but good grades are grace, bad grades aren't curses\n\nIn relationships:\nBe kind to everyone, including marginalized students\nDon't participate in malicious gossip or bullying\nBe a peacemaker in conflicts\nShow what \"love your neighbor\" looks like in action\n\nIn values:\nExpress your beliefs gently but firmly\nDon't use \"Christian jargon\" that scares people off\nPray for friends, but don't pressure them\nLive with joy and peace that makes people curious why you're different\n\nIn character building:\nLearn perseverance in difficult subjects, humility in easy ones\nCharacter development matters more than knowledge accumulation\nLearning skills equips you for service — whatever career you pursue can glorify God\n\nRemember: You might be the only Christian some classmates know. Their impression of Christianity might come from you. You don't have to be perfect, but be authentic. When you mess up, apologize courageously; when opportunities arise, share your faith naturally.",
