    "title_en": "Creation vs Evolution: Understanding Origins Debate",
    "content_zh": "创造和进化的争论很复杂，但有些关键事实需要了解。首先，区分可操作科学和历史科学——我们可以重复实验研究现在的过程，但不能穿越时间验证过去。宏观进化（从单细胞到人类）是一个关于过去的假说，不是可重复验证的科学事实。其次，宏观进化假说面临严重的科学挑战：寒武纪大爆发中几乎所有动物门类突然出现，缺乏渐进过渡化石；不可还原的复杂性表明许多生物系统无法通过渐进进化形成；DNA中的遗传信息极其复杂，自然过程从未被观察到能产生这种水平的功能性信息。第三，微观进化（物种内的适应变化，如雀喙变化、细菌抗药性）是可观察的事实，但这和从鱼到人的宏观进化是完全不同的层次。第四，虽然许多科学家接受进化假说，但科学不是投票制——许多被广泛接受的理论后来被推翻了。基督徒不必因为'多数科学家接受'就觉得必须接受。第五，关键共识：上帝是有目的的创造者，人类是特别的，生命有意义。这些远比技术细节更重要。",
    "content_en": "The creation vs evolution debate is complex, but there are key facts to understand. First, distinguish operational science from historical science — we can repeat experiments to study current processes, but can't time travel to verify the past. Macro-evolution (single cells to humans) is a hypothesis about the past, not a repeatable scientific fact. Second, the macro-evolutionary hypothesis faces serious scientific challenges: in the Cambrian Explosion nearly all animal phyla appeared suddenly without gradual transitional fossils; irreducible complexity shows many biological systems cannot form through gradual evolution; the genetic information in DNA is extraordinarily complex, and natural processes have never been observed producing this level of functional information. Third, micro-evolution (adaptive changes within species, like finch beak changes and bacterial resistance) is observable fact, but this is a completely different level from fish-to-human macro-evolution. Fourth, while many scientists accept the evolutionary hypothesis, science isn't a vote — many widely-accepted theories were later overturned. Christians need not feel they must accept something just because 'most scientists accept it.' Fifth, the key consensus: God is a purposeful Creator, humans are special, life has meaning. These matter far more than technical details.",
