    "title_en": "T.C. Chao — Reflections on Contextualization",
    "content_zh": "赵紫宸（1888-1979）是中国近代有影响力的神学家，他的故事提供了一个值得深思的教训。赵紫宸致力于让基督教信仰与中国文化对话，用中国人能理解的语言表达信仰。这个出发点是好的——保罗在雅典也用当地文化来传福音（使徒行传17章）。\n\n然而，赵紫宸的神学立场存在严重问题。他深受自由派神学影响，对圣经的权威性、基督的神性、童贞女生子、身体复活等核心教义持怀疑或否认态度。他参与了世界基督教协进会（WCC），该组织以神学自由主义著称。后来他也参与了三自爱国运动。\n\n赵紫宸的故事给我们一个重要警醒：本色化（让福音在本地文化中扎根）是必要的，但绝不能以牺牲核心教义为代价。福音确实需要用中国人能理解的方式表达，但福音的内容——基督的神性、代赎的十字架、身体的复活——不能被删减或重新定义。真正的本色化是把不变的福音用新的方式表达，而不是改变福音本身来迎合文化。",
    "content_en": "T.C. Chao (Zhao Zichen, 1888-1979) was an influential Chinese theologian whose story provides a thought-provoking lesson. Chao worked to bring Christian faith into dialogue with Chinese culture, expressing faith in language Chinese people could understand. This starting point was good — Paul did the same in Athens (Acts 17).\n\nHowever, Chao's theological positions had serious problems. Deeply influenced by liberal theology, he questioned or denied core doctrines including biblical authority, Christ's deity, the virgin birth, and bodily resurrection. He was involved with the World Council of Churches (WCC), known for theological liberalism, and later participated in the Three-Self Patriotic Movement.\n\nChao's story gives us an important warning: contextualization (rooting the Gospel in local culture) is necessary, but never at the cost of core doctrine. The Gospel does need to be expressed in culturally accessible ways, but its content — Christ's deity, the atoning cross, bodily resurrection — cannot be reduced or redefined. True contextualization expresses the unchanging Gospel in new ways, rather than changing the Gospel itself to accommodate culture.",
    "bible_verses": [
