    "title_en": "Samuel Lamb — Father of Guangzhou House Churches",
    "content_zh": "林献羔（1924-2013）是中国家庭教会运动最具代表性的人物之一。他因为坚持信仰，两次被关进监狱，总共坐了超过20年的牢。在监狱里，他被强迫做苦工，遭受各种折磨，但他从未否认基督。出狱后，他在广州自己家里开始聚会，从几个人开始，最终发展到每周上千人参加。政府多次施压要求他停止，他总是平静地说：「我必须顺从神，不顺从人。」林献羔的一生告诉我们：真正的信仰不是在舒适中才有的，而是在逼迫中也能站立得住。他的秘诀很简单——每天读经、祷告、信靠神的主权。即使在最黑暗的日子里，他相信神掌管一切。",
    "content_en": "Samuel Lamb (Lin Xiangao, 1924-2013) was one of the most iconic figures of China's house church movement. He was imprisoned twice for his faith, spending over 20 years in prison total. Behind bars, he endured forced labor and various forms of persecution, yet he never denied Christ. After release, he began meeting in his home in Guangzhou, starting with a few people and eventually growing to over a thousand weekly attendees. When authorities repeatedly pressured him to stop, he calmly replied: 'I must obey God rather than men.' Lamb's life teaches us that true faith isn't something that exists only in comfort — it stands firm under persecution. His secret was simple: daily Bible reading, prayer, and trusting God's sovereignty. Even in the darkest days, he believed God was in control.",
