    "title_zh": "杨格非 — 华中宣教巨人",
    "title_en": "Griffith John — Missionary Giant of Central China",
    "content_zh": "杨格非（1831-1912）是威尔士人，但他把一生中最好的55年都献给了中国。他1855年来到上海，后来在武汉扎根，成为华中地区最有影响力的宣教士之一。杨格非学了一口流利的中文，能用中文讲道和写作。他翻译圣经、建立教会、开办学校和医院，在战乱和疾病中从不退缩。他的妻子和几个孩子都在中国去世，但他选择留下来继续服侍。他曾说：「如果我有一千条命，我愿意把每一条都献给中国。」杨格非的故事让我们思考：什么样的爱能让一个人为异国的人民付出一切？答案是：基督的爱。当你被基督的爱抓住，你就愿意去到任何地方。",
    "content_en": "Griffith John (1831-1912) was Welsh, but he gave the best 55 years of his life to China. Arriving in Shanghai in 1855, he later settled in Wuhan and became one of the most influential missionaries in Central China. He learned fluent Chinese, preaching and writing in the language. He translated Scripture, planted churches, established schools and hospitals, never retreating despite war and disease. His wife and several children died in China, yet he chose to stay and continue serving. He once said: 'If I had a thousand lives, I would give every one to China.' His story makes us ask: What kind of love drives someone to give everything for a foreign people? The answer: the love of Christ. When Christ's love captures you, you're willing to go anywhere.",
