    "title_en": "How to Lead a Small Group Bible Study",
    "content_zh": "小组查经是门训的核心工具之一。一个好的查经不是牧师讲课，而是大家一起发现圣经的真理。最简单实用的方法是「观察-解释-应用」三步法：第一步，观察：经文说了什么？谁？什么？在哪里？什么时候？怎样？第二步，解释：经文是什么意思？为什么作者这样写？在当时的背景下意味着什么？第三步，应用：这段经文对我今天的生活有什么意义？我需要改变什么？带领小组查经的几个技巧：多问开放性问题（不是是/否），给人思考的时间，不要急着给答案，鼓励每个人参与，把讨论引回到经文本身。记住，你不需要知道所有答案——你的角色是引导大家一起寻找。",
    "content_en": "Small group Bible study is a core discipleship tool. A good study isn't a pastor lecturing — it's everyone discovering Scripture's truth together. The simplest method is 'Observe-Interpret-Apply': Step 1, Observe: What does the text say? Who? What? Where? When? How? Step 2, Interpret: What does it mean? Why did the author write this? What did it mean in its original context? Step 3, Apply: What does this passage mean for my life today? What do I need to change? Tips for leading: ask open-ended questions (not yes/no), give people time to think, don't rush to give answers, encourage everyone to participate, and keep pointing back to the text. Remember, you don't need to know all the answers — your role is guiding everyone to seek together.",
